oakcurric:unit-1147
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Groups of the periodic table"@en ;
  curric:slug "groups-of-the-periodic-table" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores how elements' reactions are related to electron arrangement and
  atomic number. It covers the properties of Groups 1, 7, and 0 and explains how these
  depend on outer electrons. It also predicts element reactivity and reactions based on
  their positions in the periodic table."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ prior learning from Patterns in the periodic
  table, where they explored how atomic structure determines element properties and reactivity
  trends. It deepens their understanding by focusing on the specific properties and reactions
  of elements in Groups 1, 7, and 0 of the periodic table. This prepares pupils for the next
  unit, Chemical analysis, where they will apply their knowledge of element groups to identify
  substances using techniques such as flame tests and instrumental methods, reinforcing their
  understanding of element behaviour and analysis.""" ;
