oakcurric:unit-569
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Photosynthesis: requirements and products"@en ;
  curric:slug "photosynthesis-requirements-and-products" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores photosynthesis as the basis for food and biomass, examines cell
  structure and adaptations in eukaryotic and prokaryotic cells, and covers the
  photosynthesis process. It focuses on using models and theories to develop hypotheses,
  interpret data, and present reasoned explanations."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit helps answer the big question, What are living things and what
  are they made of?, by examining photosynthesis, a key process where plants convert light,
  water, and carbon dioxide into glucose and oxygen, storing energy in chemical bonds. This
  understanding prepares pupils for the next unit, Aerobic and anaerobic cellular respiration,
  where they will explore how living organisms release energy from glucose, reinforcing the
  interconnected roles of photosynthesis and respiration in sustaining life.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-569-1 ,
