oakcurric:unit-491
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Circuit components"@en ;
  curric:slug "circuit-components" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores current, resistance, and potential difference. It covers
  circuit design for lamps, diodes, and thermistors, and emphasises planning experiments,
  data interpretation, and presenting scientific conclusions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ prior learning from Electric fields and
  circuit calculations, where they explored how electric fields and current flow through
  circuits. It deepens their understanding by examining the role of various circuit components,
  such as diodes, thermistors, and resistors, and how they affect circuit behaviour. This
  prepares pupils for the next unit, Mains electricity, where they will apply their knowledge
  to understand how electrical systems operate in households, including safety measures and
  energy transmission.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-491-1 ,
