oakcurric:unit-572
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Aerobic and anaerobic cellular respiration"@en ;
  curric:slug "aerobic-and-anaerobic-cellular-respiration" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit covers cellular respiration as an exothermic reaction in all cells,
  comparing aerobic and anaerobic processes. It explores cell structures and functions,
  enhanced by electron microscopy. Emphasis is on conducting experiments, analysing data,
  and interpreting results."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ prior learning from Photosynthesis:
  requirements and products, where they learned how plants produce glucose using light, water,
  and carbon dioxide. It deepens their understanding by focusing on aerobic and anaerobic
  respiration, showing how organisms release energy from glucose for life processes. This
  prepares pupils for the next unit, Transport and exchange surfaces in plants, where they will
  explore how plants transport water, minerals, and gases, reinforcing the connection between
  energy and nutrient transport.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-572-1 ,
