  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Chemical analysis"@en ;
  curric:slug "chemical-analysis" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit covers tests to identify aqueous cations and anions, including flame
  tests for metal ions like lithium, sodium, and copper. It explains the benefits of
  instrumental analysis, such as sensitivity and accuracy, and focuses on interpreting
  results from charts, tables, and spectroscopy data."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ prior learning from Groups of the periodic
  table, where they explored the properties and reactions of elements in specific groups. It
  deepens their understanding by focusing on Chemical analysis, examining techniques to
  identify substances and their composition. As the final unit in the big question, How do we
  explain how substances behave?, it reinforces pupils’ understanding of how chemical
  properties and behaviours can be analysed and applied in real-world contexts, linking element
  behaviour to practical identification methods.""" ;
