oakcurric:unit-667
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Maintaining biodiversity and human impacts"@en ;
  curric:slug "biomass-transfer-food-security-and-biodiversity" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores trophic levels, biomass pyramids, and the efficiency of biomass
  transfers in ecosystems. It examines human impacts on biodiversity, factors affecting food
  security, and biotechnological solutions. Emphasis is on evaluating environmental changes
  and ethical considerations."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ prior learning from Living organisms and their
  environments, where they explored how biotic and abiotic factors affect species survival. It
  deepens their understanding by examining the importance of maintaining biodiversity and the
  impact of human activities on ecosystems. As the final unit in the big question How do living
  things live together in their environments?, it reinforces the need for conservation and
  sustainable practices to preserve ecosystems and the complex relationships that support life.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-667-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-667-2 ,
