oakcurric:unit-899
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "DNA and the genome"@en ;
  curric:slug "dna-and-the-genome" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit covers the structure and function of eukaryotic and prokaryotic cells,
  DNA as the genetic material, and key genetic terms. It also explains protein synthesis,
  genetic variants, and how DNA structure affects proteins. The emphasis is on using models
  to explain scientific concepts."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ prior learning from Reproduction in plants,
  where they explored how genetic information is passed from one generation to the next through
  reproductive processes. It deepens their understanding by examining the structure and
  function of DNA and the genome, focusing on how genetic information is stored and expressed.
  This prepares pupils for the next unit, Inheritance, genotype and phenotype, where they will
  apply their knowledge to explore how genetic variations influence traits, reinforcing the
  principles of heredity and genetic inheritance.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-899-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-899-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-899-3 ;
  curric:id "899"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.387862Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-the-sciences-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-bq02-biology-how-do-living-things-grow-and-reproduce .

oakcurric:unit-967
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Using Earth's resources"@en ;
  curric:slug "using-earths-resources" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit covers crude oil, its role as a hydrocarbon source, and separation by
  fractional distillation. It explores cracking, metal reactivity, and extraction methods,
  including biological alternatives. Emphasis is on recycling, life-cycle assessments, and
  evaluating decisions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ prior learning from Earth's resources, where
  they explored how natural resources are used and the importance of sustainability. It deepens
  their understanding by examining the processes involved in using Earth's resources, such as
  extraction and management, and their environmental impact. This prepares pupils for the next
  unit, Atmosphere and changing climate, where they will apply their knowledge to explore how
  resource use affects the atmosphere and contributes to climate change, reinforcing the need
  for sustainable practices.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-967-1 ,
