oakcurric:unit-903
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Gene technology"@en ;
  curric:slug "gene-technology" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit covers the human genome's importance and genetic engineering, outlining
  steps, benefits, and risks. It explores gene technology in agriculture and medicine,
  focusing on ethical considerations, and societal impacts, and evaluating scientific
  limitations and risks."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ prior learning from Plant growth and
  development, where they explored how hormones regulate growth and reproduction in plants. It
  deepens their understanding by focusing on Gene technology, examining how genetic engineering
  is used to modify organisms for medical and agricultural purposes. As the final unit in the
  big question, How do living things grow and reproduce?, it reinforces pupils’ understanding
  of how genetic manipulation influences growth and reproduction, connecting natural processes
  to modern technological advances.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-903-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-903-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-903-3 ,
