oakcurric:unit-762
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Defences against pathogens, the human immune system and vaccination"@en ;
  curric:slug "defences-against-pathogens-the-human-immune-system-and-vaccination" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores the body's defences and immune response against pathogens,
  disease prevention, and vaccines. It covers plant defence responses, and disease
  detection, and evaluates scientific applications, considering personal, social, economic,
  and environmental implications."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ prior learning from Health and disease, where
  they explored the relationship between lifestyle factors and disease. It deepens their
  understanding by examining the body's defences against pathogens, focusing on the immune
  system and how vaccines help prevent diseases. This prepares pupils for the next unit,
  Medicines and new treatments for disease, where they will apply their knowledge to explore
  how modern medicines, such as antibiotics and monoclonal antibodies, are used to treat
  diseases, reinforcing their understanding of disease prevention and treatment.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-762-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-762-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-762-3 ,
