  limited number of related specialised cells."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350318Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-specialised-cell
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "specialised cell"@en ;
  schema:description """A differentiated cell that is adapted to carry out a particular
  function."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350325Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-immune-rejection
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "immune rejection"@en ;
  schema:description """When a patient’s immune system attacks non-self cells (e.g.
  transplants)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350329Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-ethical
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "ethical"@en ;
  schema:description """An ethical issue relates to whether an action and its consequences are right
  or wrong."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350334Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-climate-change
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "climate change"@en ;
  schema:description "a long-term change in Earth’s climate patterns"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350396Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-osmosis
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "osmosis"@en ;
  schema:description """the net movement of water molecules through a selectively-permeable membrane
  from high to low concentration of water molecules"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350444Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-net-movement
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "net movement"@en ;
  schema:description "the overall movement of particles"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350450Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-active-transport
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "active transport"@en ;
  schema:description """the net movement of particles against a concentration gradient using
  energy"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350455Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-concentration-gradient
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "concentration gradient"@en ;
  schema:description "a difference in the concentration of particles from one area to another"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350460Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-root-hair-cell
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "root hair cell"@en ;
  schema:description """a specialised plant cell found in the roots that absorb water and nutrients
  into the plant"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350468Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-atom
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "atom"@en ;
  schema:description "An atom is the building block of all matter."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350583Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-element
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "element"@en ;
  schema:description "Each element is made up of only one type of atom."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350588Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-empirical-formula
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "empirical formula"@en ;
  schema:description "The simplest whole number ratio of atoms of each element in a compound."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350604Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-polyatomic-ions
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "polyatomic ions"@en ;
  schema:description "Ions that are made up of more than one type of atom."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350608Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-ide
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "\"–ide\""@en ;
  schema:description """The name ending for a compound with a metal and non–metal present, for
  example, potassium iodide (KI)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350613Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-ate
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "\"–ate\""@en ;
  schema:description """The name ending for a compound with three or more elements present (one of
  which is oxygen), for example, potassium sulfate (K₂SO₄)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350620Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-heating
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "heating"@en ;
  schema:description "causes the particles of a substance to move or vibrate more rapidly"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350624Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-thermal-conduction
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "thermal conduction"@en ;
  schema:description """the transfer of energy through a material due to collisions between moving
  or vibrating particles"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350629Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-thermal-insulation
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "thermal insulation"@en ;
  schema:description "reduces the transfer of energy by thermal conduction"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350633Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-thermal-conductors
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "thermal conductors"@en ;
  schema:description "substances that transfer energy by thermal conduction quickly"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350637Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-thermal-insulators
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "thermal insulators"@en ;
  schema:description """substances that transfer energy by thermal conduction slowly or not
  at all"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350642Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-hormone
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "hormone"@en ;
  schema:description "chemicals released by plants that regulate their growth"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350646Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-compound
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "compound"@en ;
  schema:description """A compound is made of two or more different elements chemically bonded
  together."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350670Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-chemical-formula
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "chemical formula"@en ;
  schema:description """The chemical formula of a molecule is a shorthand way of listing the type
  and number of atoms in a compound."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350675Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-chemical-composition
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "chemical composition"@en ;
  schema:description """The chemical composition tells you the different types of atoms in a
  chemical."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350682Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-mixture
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "mixture"@en ;
  schema:description """A mixture is a material that contains two or more different substances that
  can be physically separated."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350689Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-separate
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "separate"@en ;
  schema:description """In chemistry, to separate something is to extract and isolate a substance
  from a mixture."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350695Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-property
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "property"@en ;
  schema:description """A property is a feature or characteristic of a substance that can be used to
  classify it or describe how it behaves."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350700Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-wave-medium
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "wave medium"@en ;
  schema:description "the wave medium is the material that a wave can move through."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350747Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-displacement
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "displacement"@en ;
  schema:description """displacement at a point of a wave is the distance that the wave medium is
  from its rest position."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350752Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-period-of-a-wave
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "period (of a wave)"@en ;
  schema:description """period (of a wave), T, is the time for a complete wave to pass any point,
  which is the same as the time to make one complete wave."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350756Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-frequency
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "frequency"@en ;
  schema:description """frequency is the number of waves produced each second. Frequency is measured
  in Hertz (Hz)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.350761Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-power
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "power"@en ;
  schema:description "having control or authority over something or someone"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.351112Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-dna
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "DNA"@en ;
  schema:description """DNA is the chemical substance that genetic material is made out of; it
  stores the genetic code."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.351286Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-double-helix
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "double helix"@en ;
  schema:description "DNA has a double helix structure made from two chains in a spiral."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.351295Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-genome
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "genome"@en ;
  schema:description "The genome is all of the genetic material of a cell."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.351299Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-temperature
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "temperature"@en ;
  schema:description """a measure of how hot a substance is; it is related to the kinetic energy of
  the individual particles"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.351318Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-specific-heat-capacity
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "specific heat capacity"@en ;
  schema:description """the change in internal energy when the temperature of 1 kg of the material
  changes by 1°C"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.351325Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-internal-energy
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "internal energy"@en ;
  schema:description """the sum of the kinetic energy and potential energy of the particles
  something is made of"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.351335Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-kinetic-energy
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "kinetic energy"@en ;
  schema:description "the energy an object has because of it's motion"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:02.351342Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-potential-energy
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "potential energy"@en ;
  schema:description """the energy an object has because of its position and the forces
